\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

-module.
 Then 
\begin_inset Formula $M\otimes_{A}\widehat{A}\cong\widehat{M}$
\end_inset

.
 Especially, if 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is complete, then 
\begin_inset Formula $M$
\end_inset

 is complete, that is, 
\begin_inset Formula $M=\widehat{M}$
\end_inset

.
 In particular, 
\begin_inset Formula $A/I$
\end_inset

 is complete if 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is complete.
 
